# Player OS instruments

Before any **Player UX / layout / pixel** change:

1. Read [`docs/vision/PLAYER_OS_INSTRUMENT_TAXONOMY.md`](../../docs/vision/PLAYER_OS_INSTRUMENT_TAXONOMY.md) — classify the band (Identity, Directive, Navigation, Progression, Telemetry, Execute).
2. Read [`docs/vision/AGENT_PLAYER_UX_SPRINT_TEMPLATE.md`](../../docs/vision/AGENT_PLAYER_UX_SPRINT_TEMPLATE.md) — set cohesion scope (Frame | Inner | Both).

## Frame vs inner

- **Cohesion = shared frame** — `header → pd-os-deck → __well → inner`. One deck grammar across HQ bands. Never new skins per section.
- **Differentiation = inner only** — holo card, hero mission, nav tile, pathway track, radar well, terminal brackets differ inside the slot.

## Reject

- Route-only UX without instrument type
- Navigation tile chrome on Telemetry surfaces
- Pathway-only accent systems that break the shared frame
